phrases: TL Note: Tanabe Akira is the editor of the Kannagi comic, and he decides the vital parts about the plot, thus he had to be persuaded to make it a'maid cafe' chapter.
TL Note: (fujoshi=rotten woman) refers to female otaku, particularly those interested in yaoi or boy's love.
It is derived from the word (fujoshi=lady)
TL Note: That is about 13 years old.
TL Note: A title typical of a gal-game.
Maid cafe Maidia Zange-chan Commemoration for newcomer Zange-chan Rice In Service Letters on the Rice: Zange
We are having a special event
Do you have to do something later?
Then can you help me with some shopping?
Then let us meet at the entrance of Hip Walk at 2:00PM.
Yes, he said he will be counting on you.
I have no experience shopping at such places.
I would have no idea how to do it correctly.
What do you want to get?
A complete set of underwear too!
If possible, shoes or a bag...
I also want to look at some accessories as well.
So, what is your budget like?
If there is any left over, I will treat you to something!
Why are all of them so expensive?
This shop is already quite cheap!
Gosh, she does not know anything about the market price...
What kind of wealthy lifestyle has she been living?
If I put a glittery heart-shaped keyholder sold at 100-yen shops on this bag,
can I insist that it is from Sama*tha Thava*a?
If you talk about Sama*tha Thava*a while wearing those anime clothes,
our already few number of female viewers will snicker.
What does he expect me to do with this?
Right now, I can barely change my clothes.
You are a god, are not you?
Cannot you just make clothes appear?
Do not ask for the impossible!
I am wearing these clothes merely because they materalized along with my human figure.
But you should have Tsugumi take you along on matters like this.
I was a fool to be so ecstatic!
Jin is such a penny-pinching miser!
Does he expect me get by with three sets of jerseys?!
Well, guys tend to go for the cheap stuff.
Hey, you wanted to look at some underwear too, right?
Let us go take a look.
I never knew underwear came in so many shapes!
These are completely different from the ones that I am wearing!
Jin should have bought this kind for me from the start.
Yeah, I think those feminine ones suit you!
Miss, you can try them on.
Tsugumi-san, what is your cup size?
My size fluctuates between B and C.
And how I especially become a C after I get fat...
This is Tsugumi, 15 years old, talking!
But Nagi-san is clearly smaller than me.
I may offend her if I tell her the truth.
Well, that is average among the Japanese.
Since this bra is so roomy, that must mean...
I must not think too deeply about it!
If you are going to buy one, the prices over here are just right.
What is this sense of defeat I am feeling?!
Am I rubbing salt into her wound?
Gosh, Tsugumi, you are such a tactless woman!
where is my size, a B-cup?
Oh yeah, that is just about right.
Even though I say it is B, it is rather closer to C, I think...
Taking into account my growth in future, perhaps I can even go for a C.
Is this your first time here?
With your body, D might be too small for you.
There are many girls who wear smaller sizes because they are shy.
But it is recommended to wear a size that fits your body...
Pardon me, but may I ask how old are you?
I am a first year junior high student.
I think you should choose a larger size.
I will persuade Jin and get my revenge next time!
Next time, shall we visit a cheaper shop nearby?
You cannot wear three sets of jerseys all the time, right?
A girl needs a lot of things.
Three sets of jerseys is too little!
I will talk to Jin as well.
Should I get a part-time job?
I am thinking of going to a maid cafe.
Perhaps we can go if we ask the person-in-charge, Tanabe-san.
Leave such inside jokes to the commentary!
But do not those shops only exist near the capital?
A maid cafe even opened up in this city.
While that does raise the question of Why only now?, it is still a surprise.
But why do you want to go?
If you ask me, that place is more for guys...
Only at a maid cafe can I rightfully stare at cute girls in frilly clothes.
It is just like you to think like that.
But if you like frilly clothes, you can just wear them yourself...
I want to look at cute girls wearing the clothes!
I am hesitant about actually going.
You see, otaku-culture is a bit unique, is not it?
So I am wondering if I can get an expert to escort me there...
Since just now, I have been trying very hard not to get involved in your discussion...
But why do you assume that all otaku are knowledgeable in that area?!
You mean it is not true?
You are wrong if you think that all otaku go moe!
Misunderstandings arise when the media stereotypes the entire population based on a small minority!
Even the pronunciation is wrong to begin with!
If I nudge him in this way, he will talk a lot.
I have never heard anyone say moe like that!
Or should I say, are not those people just non-otaku making fun of us?
In the first place, who the hell would address an otaku as an otaku?
Hey, is it all right for me to go to a maid cafe?
There are many female customers anyway.
People who are not otaku also come often because they find the place unusual.
Let us set the date for this Sunday then.
I am really glad Nagi is not here today.
I do not want to teach her this kind of weird culture.
Why did you choose to meet here?
It is closer than the train station.
You did not bring Nagi-sama along?
Obviously I could not bring her!
Well then, Akiba-kun, be sure to explain things thoroughly for us!
That is why I called you here.
But do not you seniors know a lot as well?
Well, it is true that I am a female.
If you are not, it is fine.
In fact, just stay the way you are.
Takako-senpai in her home clothes looks just like an office lady.
Looks like they are wearing maid clothes that do not look like maid clothes.
This is the cosplay of Kamatte Pure Heart Trois Sunao Ni Narenai!
Looks like they are having a tie-up event.
They do this often for the publicity as well as fans of the game.
My, I guess we are lucky then.
I came here to look at maid uniforms-
But this is not so bad.
I will take you to your seats!
This is the first time I am seeing a cosplay.
So, what kind of sci-fi battle fantasy game is this?
No, it is just a modern-day drama...
Who would wear such unbelievable clothing in modern time?!
Now that is something you should not say.
Please place your orders if you have decided.
I will have an iced coffee.
I will have this apple cinnamon tea.
I was looking at the menu, so I did not really notice...
And so is everyone from the Arts Club!
My friend got sick all of a sudden, but even so,
I should not have taken her place for her part-time job!
If they see me in such embarrassing clothes...
Furthermore, Nagi-san just happened to be working here...
I am such an idiot to think that I would not run into friends just because it is a maid cafe!
I kept it from him because I am sure he would object to me doing a part-time job.
If this continues, we will have a big fight when we get home.
At worst, I may even get driven out!
You cannot keep the customers waiting!
She looks like Arzelede-sama in every aspect!
The hair being genuine is amazing!
This is the first time I have seen one look that well replicated!
This kind of cosplay is limited to beauties!
Is not the girl next to her good-looking as well?
Her hairdo says she is Malon-chan, right?
That girl has the same air about her!
I am talking about her politeness when serving the customers and her lack of confidence!
I am so glad to have been a KamaPure fan!
Hey, why is Tsugumi here as well?
A child caught in a trick?
I was so amazed at the excellent quality that before I knew it...
I was so amazed at the glamor and cuteness that before I knew it...
Why were you not surprised first that she was someone you knew?
That aside, what kind of surprise is this?
Mikuriya, you were trying to surprise us!
Here are your iced coffees and apple cinnamon tea.
It-It is not like I am doing this kind of part-time job because I want to!
I am only taking my friend's place because she cannot show up.
Can I take a photo with you?
I would like to place an order!
But it is certainly an effective method.
With this, she can get devotees in a short time.
I should not let her do as she likes.
Under the same conditions, I can collect more devotees than her.
I look better in maid clothes!
I will interfere with her business and make her reputation drop!
Excuse me, but which KamaPure character do you like?
The gap in her nobility and her clumsiness makes her cute.
She is doing her job far better than expected.
As a clumsy character, she is functioning pretty well.
Do not just go to the other tables!
You have to let Mikuriya see you better too.
I cannot look at her in the eyes when she is this close.
Jin, are you mad at me?
I am telling you not to come near me!
Even though he was staring at her just now.
What is going on with that group?
You must be mad that I took on a part-time job without your permission, right?
But Jin, I am doing it for you-
So I cannot look at you straight, so I am telling you to stand back!
At the maid cafe, a great shout of joy and embarrassment!
To do that in front of Tsugumi-chan-
I thought I could catch up with you...
I just wanted to earn my own allowance.
I wasted some money the other day...
I can also gather devotees outside of school...
I am sorry for keeping quiet.
But if you tell me to quit, I will quit.
I did not like it when you got your pictures taken.
You looked like you were enjoying it.
since you say so, I will quit.
She was the most popular here.
I even canceled my job at the TV station for this part-time job!
I cannot do anything about that.
There is no point if Nee-sama is not here!
I will not allow you to quit!
With a local talent like you, our shop will run smoothly!
Manager, you are stronger than I thought!
Please watch the next episode of Kannagi too!
